#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><informaltable><tgroup><tbody><row><entry><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:665 l10n/source/edge.xml:4182
msgid "SUSE Linux Micro"
msgstr "SUSE Linux Micro"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:666
msgid ""
"See <link xl:href=\"https://documentation.suse.com/sle-micro/6.1/\">SUSE "
"Linux Micro official documentation</link>"
msgstr ""
"请参见 <link xl:href=\"https://documentation.suse.com/sle-micro/6.1/\">SUSE "
"Linux Micro 官方文档</link>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><blockquote><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:667
msgid ""
"SUSE Linux Micro is a lightweight and secure operating system for the edge. "
"It merges the enterprise-hardened components of SUSE Linux Enterprise with "
"the features that developers want in a modern, immutable operating system. "
"As a result, you get a reliable infrastructure platform with best-in-class "
"compliance that is also simple to use."
msgstr ""
"SUSE Linux Micro 是一个安全的轻量级边缘操作系统。它将 SUSE Linux Enterprise "
"强化组件与开发人员需要的各种功能融入一套不可变的新式操作系统，从而形成一个可"
"靠的基础架构平台，不仅具有同类最佳的合规性，而且易于使用。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:668
msgid "How does SUSE Edge use SUSE Linux Micro?"
msgstr "SUSE Edge 如何使用 SUSE Linux Micro？"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:669
msgid ""
"We use SUSE Linux Micro as the base operating system for our platform stack. "
"This provides us with a secure, stable and minimal base for building upon."
msgstr "我们使用 SUSE Linux Micro "
"作为平台堆栈的基础操作系统。它为我们提供了安全、稳定且精简的构建基础。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:670
msgid ""
"SUSE Linux Micro is unique in its use of file system (Btrfs) snapshots to "
"allow for easy rollbacks in case something goes wrong with an upgrade. This "
"allows for secure remote upgrades for the entire platform even without "
"physical access in case of issues."
msgstr ""
"SUSE Linux Micro 的独特之处在于它使用了文件系统 (Btrfs) "
"快照，一旦在升级期间出错，我们就可以轻松回滚。这样，在出现问题时，即使无法进"
"行物理访问，也可以对整个平台安全地进行远程升级。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:672 l10n/source/edge.xml:846
msgid "Installation media"
msgstr "安装媒体"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:673
msgid ""
"SUSE Edge uses the Edge Image Builder (<xref linkend=\"components-eib\"/>) "
"to preconfigure the SUSE Linux Micro self-install installation image."
msgstr ""
"SUSE Edge 使用 Edge Image Builder（<xref linkend=\"components-eib\"/>）"
"来预配置 SUSE Linux Micro 自安装映像。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:674
msgid "Local administration"
msgstr "本地管理"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:675
msgid ""
"SUSE Linux Micro comes with Cockpit to allow the local management of the "
"host through a Web application."
msgstr "SUSE Linux Micro 附带 Cockpit，让您可以通过 Web 应用程序对主机进行本地管理。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:676
msgid ""
"This service is disabled by default but can be started by enabling the "
"systemd service <literal>cockpit.socket</literal>."
msgstr "此服务默认已禁用，但可以通过启用 systemd 服务 <literal>cockpit.socket</"
"literal> 来启动。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:678
msgid ""
"There is no desktop environment available in SUSE Linux Micro at the moment "
"but a containerized solution is in development."
msgstr "SUSE Linux Micro 目前不提供桌面环境，但我们正在开发容器化解决方案。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><informaltable><tgroup><tbody><row><entry><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:679 l10n/source/edge.xml:702 l10n/source/edge.xml:4218
msgid "Metal<superscript>3</superscript>"
msgstr "Metal<superscript>3</superscript>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:680
msgid ""
"<link xl:href=\"https://metal3.io/\">Metal<superscript>3</superscript></"
"link> is a CNCF project which provides bare-metal infrastructure management "
"capabilities for Kubernetes."
msgstr ""
"<link xl:href=\"https://metal3.io/\">Metal<superscript>3</superscript></"
"link> 是一个 CNCF 项目，它为 Kubernetes 提供裸机基础架构管理功能。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:683
msgid "How does SUSE Edge use Metal<superscript>3</superscript>?"
msgstr "SUSE Edge 如何使用 Metal<superscript>3</superscript>？"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:685
msgid ""
"This method provides declarative APIs that enable inventory and state "
"management of bare-metal servers, including automated inspection, cleaning "
"and provisioning/deprovisioning."
msgstr "此方法提供声明性 API "
"来对裸机服务器进行清单和状态管理，包括自动检查、清理和置备/取消置备。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:687
