#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1324 l10n/source/edge.xml:1371
msgid "Why use MetalLB"
msgstr "为何使用 MetalLB"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1325 l10n/source/edge.xml:1372
msgid ""
"MetalLB is a compelling choice for load balancing in bare-metal Kubernetes "
"clusters for several reasons:"
msgstr "由于以下原因，MetalLB 成为了用来实现裸机 Kubernetes 群集负载平衡的较佳选择："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1326 l10n/source/edge.xml:1373
msgid ""
"Native Integration with Kubernetes: MetalLB seamlessly integrates with "
"Kubernetes, making it easy to deploy and manage using familiar Kubernetes "
"tools and practices."
msgstr ""
"与 Kubernetes 本机集成：MetalLB 可无缝与 Kubernetes 集成，让用户可使用熟悉的 "
"Kubernetes 工具和方法轻松进行部署和管理。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1327 l10n/source/edge.xml:1374
msgid ""
"Bare-Metal Compatibility: Unlike cloud-based load balancers, MetalLB is "
"designed specifically for on-premises deployments where traditional load "
"balancers might not be available or feasible."
msgstr "裸机兼容性：与基于云的负载平衡器不同，MetalLB "
"专门用于本地部署，在这种部署中，可能无法使用传统负载平衡器或使用传统负载平衡"
"器不现实。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1328
msgid ""
"Supports Multiple Protocols: MetalLB supports both Layer 2 and BGP (Border "
"Gateway Protocol) modes, providing flexibility for different network "
"architectures and requirements."
msgstr "支持多种协议：MetalLB 支持 Layer 2 和 "
"BGP（边界网关协议）模式，提供了很大的灵活性，适合不同的网络架构并可满足不同的"
"要求。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1329 l10n/source/edge.xml:1376
msgid ""
"High Availability: By distributing load-balancing responsibilities across "
"multiple nodes, MetalLB ensures high availability and reliability for your "
"services."
msgstr "高可用性：MetalLB "
"可以将负载平衡负担分散在多个节点中，从而确保服务的高可用性和可靠性。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1330 l10n/source/edge.xml:1377
msgid ""
"Scalability: MetalLB can handle large-scale deployments, scaling alongside "
"your Kubernetes cluster to meet increasing demand."
msgstr "可伸缩性：MetalLB 可以处理大规模部署，并且能够将 Kubernetes "
"群集扩容来满足日益增长的需求。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1331 l10n/source/edge.xml:1378
msgid ""
"In layer 2 mode, one node assumes the responsibility of advertising a "
"service to the local network. From the network’s perspective, it simply "
"looks like that machine has multiple IP addresses assigned to its network "
"interface."
msgstr "在第 2 层模式下，一个节点负责向本地网络播发服务。从网络的角度看，"
"似乎为该计算机的网络接口分配了多个 IP 地址。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1332 l10n/source/edge.xml:1379
msgid ""
"The major advantage of the layer 2 mode is its universality: it works on any "
"Ethernet network, with no special hardware required, not even fancy routers."
msgstr "第 2 "
"层模式的主要优势在于其通用性：它可以在任何以太网上正常工作，不需要任何特殊硬"
"件，甚至不需要各种形式的路由器。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1333
msgid "MetalLB on K3s (using L2)"
msgstr "K3s 上的 MetalLB（使用 L2）"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1334
msgid ""
"In this quick start, L2 mode will be used.  This means we do not need any "
"special network equipment but three free IPs within the network range."
msgstr "本快速入门将使用 L2 模式。这意味着我们不需要任何特殊网络设备，"
"只需使用网络范围内的三个空闲 IP。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1336 l10n/source/edge.xml:1383
msgid "A K3s cluster where MetalLB is going to be deployed."
msgstr "要部署 MetalLB 的 K3s 群集。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><warning><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1337
msgid ""
"K3S comes with its own service load balancer named Klipper. You <link "
"xl:href=\"https://metallb.universe.tf/configuration/k3s/\">need to disable "
"it to run MetalLB</link>. To disable Klipper, K3s needs to be installed "
"using the <literal>--disable=servicelb</literal> flag."
msgstr ""
"K3S 自身附带服务负载平衡器（名为 Klipper）。需要<link xl:href="
"\"https://metallb.universe.tf/configuration/k3s/\">禁用 Klipper 才能运行 "
"MetalLB</link>。要禁用 Klipper，需使用 <literal>--disable=servicelb</"
"literal> 标志安装 K3s。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1339
msgid ""
"Three free IP adressess within the network range. In this example "
"<literal>192.168.122.10-192.168.122.12</literal>"
msgstr ""
"网络范围内的三个空闲 IP 地址。在本示例中为 "
"<literal>192.168.122.10-192.168.122.12</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><important><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1340
msgid ""
"You must make sure these IP addresses are unassigned.  In a DHCP environment "
"these addresses must not be part of the DHCP pool to avoid dual assignments."
msgstr "必须确保这三个 IP 地址未被分配。在 DHCP 环境中，为了避免出现双重分配情况，"
"不得将这些地址添加到 DHCP 池中。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1342 l10n/source/edge.xml:1390
msgid ""
"We will be using the MetalLB Helm chart published as part of the SUSE Edge "
