"Currently, there are two ways to perform \"Day 2\" operations on your "
"<literal>management</literal> cluster:"
msgstr "目前，可以通过两种方式在<literal>管理</literal>群集上执行“Day 2”操作："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1809
msgid ""
"Through <xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller\"/> - <xref "
"linkend=\"management-day2-upgrade-controller\"/>"
msgstr ""
"通过 <xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller\"/> - <xref linkend"
"=\"management-day2-upgrade-controller\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1810
msgid ""
"Through <xref linkend=\"components-fleet\"/> - <xref linkend=\"management-"
"day2-fleet\"/>"
msgstr ""
"通过 <xref linkend=\"components-fleet\"/> - <xref linkend=\"management-day2-"
"fleet\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><important><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1812
msgid ""
"The <literal>Upgrade Controller</literal> currently only supports "
"<literal>Day 2</literal> operations for <emphasis role=\"strong\">non air-"
"gapped management</emphasis> clusters."
msgstr ""
"<literal>升级控制器</literal>目前仅支持<emphasis role=\"strong\">非隔离管理</"
"emphasis>群集的 <literal>Day 2</literal> 操作。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1813
msgid ""
"This section covers how to perform the various <literal>Day 2</literal> "
"operations related to upgrading your <literal>management</literal> cluster "
"from one Edge platform version to another."
msgstr ""
"本节介绍如何执行与将<literal>管理</literal>群集从一个 Edge "
"平台版本升级到另一个版本相关的各种 <literal>Day 2</literal> 操作。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1814
msgid ""
"The <literal>Day 2</literal> operations are automated by the Upgrade "
"Controller (<xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller\"/>) and include:"
msgstr ""
"<literal>Day 2</literal> 操作由升级控制器（<xref linkend=\"components-"
"upgrade-controller\"/>）自动执行，包括："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1815
msgid "SUSE Linux Micro (<xref linkend=\"components-slmicro\"/>) OS upgrade"
msgstr "SUSE Linux Micro（<xref linkend=\"components-slmicro\"/>）操作系统升级"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1816
msgid ""
"<xref linkend=\"components-rke2\"/> or <xref linkend=\"components-k3s\"/> "
"Kubernetes upgrade"
msgstr ""
"<xref linkend=\"components-rke2\"/>或<xref linkend=\"components-k3s\"/"
">Kubernetes 升级"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1817
msgid ""
"SUSE additional components (SUSE Rancher Prime, SUSE Security, etc.) upgrade"
msgstr "其他 SUSE 组件（SUSE Rancher Prime、SUSE Security 等）升级"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1819
msgid ""
"Before upgrading your <literal>management</literal> cluster, the following "
"prerequisites must be met:"
msgstr "升级<literal>管理</literal>群集之前，必须满足以下先决条件："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1820
msgid ""
"<literal>SCC registered nodes</literal> - ensure your cluster nodes' OS are "
"registered with a subscription key that supports the OS version specified in "
"the Edge release (<xref linkend=\"release-notes\"/>) you intend to upgrade "
"to."
msgstr ""
"<literal>已在 SCC 中注册的节点</literal> - "
"确保群集节点的操作系统已使用相应的订阅密钥注册，且该密钥支持要升级到的 Edge "
"版本中指定的操作系统版本（<xref linkend=\"release-notes\"/>）。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1821
msgid ""
"<literal>Upgrade Controller</literal> - make sure that the <literal>Upgrade "
"Controller</literal> has been deployed on your <literal>management</literal> "
"cluster. For installation steps, refer to <xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-"
"controller-installation\"/>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>升级控制器</literal> - "
"确保<literal>管理</literal>群集上已部署<literal>升级控制器</literal>。有关安"
"装步骤，请参见<xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller-installation\""
"/>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1822
msgid "Upgrade"
msgstr "升级"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1823
msgid ""
"Determine the Edge release (<xref linkend=\"release-notes\"/>) version that "
"you wish to upgrade your <literal>management</literal> cluster to."
msgstr ""
"确定要将<literal>管理</literal>群集升级到哪个 Edge 版本（<xref linkend"
"=\"release-notes\"/>）。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1824
msgid ""
"In the <literal>management</literal> cluster, deploy an "
"<literal>UpgradePlan</literal> that specifies the desired <literal>release "
"version</literal>. The <literal>UpgradePlan</literal> must be deployed in "
"the namespace of the <literal>Upgrade Controller</literal>."
msgstr ""
"在<literal>管理</literal>群集中，部署一个指定目标<literal>版本</literal>的 "
"<literal>UpgradePlan</literal>。<literal>UpgradePlan</literal> "
"必须部署在<literal>升级控制器</literal>的名称空间中。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1825
msgid ""
"There may be use-cases where you would want to make additional "
"configurations over the <literal>UpgradePlan</literal>. For all possible "
"configurations, refer to <xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller-"
"extensions-upgrade-plan\"/>."
msgstr ""
"某些情况下，除了 <literal>UpgradePlan</literal> "
"之外，您可能还想进行其他配置。有关所有可能的配置，请参见<xref linkend"
"=\"components-upgrade-controller-extensions-upgrade-plan\"/>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1826
msgid ""
"Deploying the <literal>UpgradePlan</literal> to the <literal>Upgrade "
"Controller’s</literal> namespace will begin the <literal>upgrade process</"
"literal>."
msgstr ""
"将 <literal>UpgradePlan</literal> "
"部署到<literal>升级控制器</literal>的名称空间后，<literal>升级过程</literal>"
"即会开始。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1827
msgid ""
"For more information on the actual <literal>upgrade process</literal>, refer "
"to <xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller-how\"/>."
msgstr ""
"有关实际<literal>升级过程</literal>的详细信息，请参见<xref linkend"
"=\"components-upgrade-controller-how\"/>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1828
msgid ""
"For information on how to track the <literal>upgrade process</literal>, "
"refer to <xref linkend=\"components-upgrade-controller-how-track\"/>."
msgstr ""
"有关如何跟踪<literal>升级过程</literal>的信息，请参见<xref linkend"
"=\"components-upgrade-controller-how-track\"/>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1830 l10n/source/edge.xml:2339
msgid ""
"This section offers information on how to perform \"Day 2\" operations using "
"the Fleet (<xref linkend=\"components-fleet\"/>) component."
msgstr "本节提供有关如何使用 Fleet（<xref linkend=\"components-fleet\"/>）组件执行“"
"Day 2”操作的信息。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1832
msgid ""
"<xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-components\"/> - default components "
"used for all \"Day 2\" operations."
msgstr ""
"<xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-components\"/> - 执行所有“Day "
"2”操作需要使用的默认组件。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1833
msgid ""
"<xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-determine-use-case\"/> - provides an "
"overview of the Fleet custom resources that will be used and their "
"suitability for different \"Day 2\" operations use-cases."
msgstr ""
"<xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-determine-use-case\"/> - 概述将使用的 "
"Fleet 自定义资源及其在不同“Day 2”操作场景中的适用性。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1834
msgid ""
"<xref linkend=\"management-day2-upgrade-workflow\"/> - provides a workflow "
"guide for executing \"Day 2\" operations with Fleet."
msgstr ""
"<xref linkend=\"management-day2-upgrade-workflow\"/> - 提供使用 Fleet 执行“"
"Day 2”操作的工作流程指南。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1835
msgid ""
"<xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-os-upgrade\"/> - describes how to do "
"OS upgrades using Fleet."
msgstr ""
"<xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-os-upgrade\"/> - 说明如何使用 Fleet "
"进行操作系统升级。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1836
msgid ""
"<xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-k8s-upgrade\"/> - describes how to do "
"Kubernetes version upgrades using Fleet."
msgstr ""
"<xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-k8s-upgrade\"/> - 说明如何使用 Fleet "
"进行 Kubernetes 版本升级。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1837
msgid ""
"<xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-helm-upgrade\"/> - describes how to do "
"Helm chart upgrades using Fleet."
msgstr ""
"<xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-helm-upgrade\"/> - 说明如何使用 Fleet "
"进行 Helm chart 升级。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1839
msgid ""
"Below you can find a description of the default components that should be "
"set up on your <literal>management</literal> cluster so that you can "
"successfully perform \"Day 2\" operations using Fleet."
msgstr "下文将介绍为使用 Fleet 顺利执行“Day "
"2”操作而应在<literal>管理</literal>群集上设置的默认组件。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1841
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Optional</emphasis>; Responsible for managing "
"<literal>downstream clusters</literal> and deploying the <literal>System "
"Upgrade Controller</literal> on your <literal>management cluster</literal>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\""
">可选</emphasis>组件；负责管理<literal>下游群集</literal>并在<literal>管理群"
"集</literal>上部署<literal>系统升级控制器</literal>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1842
msgid "For more information, see <xref linkend=\"components-rancher\"/>."
msgstr "有关详细信息，请参见<xref linkend=\"components-rancher\"/>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1843 l10n/source/edge.xml:2349
msgid "System Upgrade Controller (SUC)"
msgstr "系统升级控制器 (SUC)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1844 l10n/source/edge.xml:2351
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">System Upgrade Controller</emphasis> is "
"responsible for executing tasks on specified nodes based on configuration "
"data provided through a custom resource, called a <literal>Plan</literal>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\""
">系统升级控制器</emphasis>负责根据通过名为<literal>计划</literal>的自定义资源"
"提供的配置数据，在指定节点上执行任务。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1845 l10n/source/edge.xml:2352
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">SUC</emphasis> is actively utilized to upgrade the "
"operating system and Kubernetes distribution."
msgstr ""
"系统会主动利用 <emphasis role=\"strong\">SUC</emphasis> 升级操作系统和 "
"Kubernetes 发行版。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1846 l10n/source/edge.xml:2353
msgid ""
"For more information about the <emphasis role=\"strong\">SUC</emphasis> "
"component and how it fits in the Edge stack, see <xref linkend=\"components-"
"system-upgrade-controller\"/>."
msgstr ""
"有关 <emphasis role=\"strong\">SUC</emphasis> 组件及其如何安置到 Edge "
"堆栈中的详细信息，请参见<xref linkend=\"components-system-upgrade-"
"controller\"/>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1847 l10n/source/edge.xml:2355
msgid "Determine your use-case"
msgstr "确定您的使用场景"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1848 l10n/source/edge.xml:2356
msgid ""
"Fleet uses two types of <link xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/"
"extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/\">custom resources</link> "
"to enable the management of Kubernetes and Helm resources."
msgstr ""
"Fleet 使用两种<link xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/"
"extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/\">自定义资源</"
"link>来实现对 Kubernetes 和 Helm 资源的管理。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1849 l10n/source/edge.xml:2357
msgid ""
"Below you can find information about the purpose of these resources and the "
"use-cases they are best suited for in the context of \"Day 2\" operations."
msgstr "下文将介绍这些资源的用途，以及在“Day 2”操作情境中它们最适合的使用场景。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1850 l10n/source/edge.xml:2197
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2358 l10n/source/edge.xml:2694
msgid "GitRepo"
msgstr "GitRepo"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1851 l10n/source/edge.xml:2359
msgid ""
"A <literal>GitRepo</literal> is a Fleet (<xref linkend=\"components-fleet\"/"
">) resource that represents a Git repository from which <literal>Fleet</"
"literal> can create <literal>Bundles</literal>. Each <literal>Bundle</"
"literal> is created based on configuration paths defined inside of the "
"<literal>GitRepo</literal> resource. For more information, see the <link "
"xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/gitrepo-add\">GitRepo</link> "
"documentation."
msgstr ""
"<literal>GitRepo</literal> 是一种 Fleet（<xref linkend=\"components-fleet\""
"/>）资源，它代表一个 Git 储存库，<literal>Fleet</literal> "
"可从中创建<literal>捆绑包</literal>。每个<literal>捆绑包</literal>都是基于 "
"<literal>GitRepo</literal> 资源中定义的配置路径创建的。有关详细信息，请参见 "
"<link xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/gitrepo-add\">GitRepo</link> 文档。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1852 l10n/source/edge.xml:2360
msgid ""
"In the context of \"Day 2\" operations, <literal>GitRepo</literal> resources "
"are normally used to deploy <literal>SUC</literal> or <literal>SUC Plans</"
"literal> in <emphasis role=\"strong\">non air-gapped</emphasis> environments "
"that utilize a <emphasis>Fleet GitOps</emphasis> approach."
msgstr ""
"在“Day 2”操作情境中，<literal>GitRepo</literal> 资源通常用于在利用 "
"<emphasis>Fleet GitOps</emphasis> 方法的<emphasis role=\"strong\">非隔离</"
"emphasis>环境中部署 <literal>SUC</literal> 或 <literal>SUC 计划</literal>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1853 l10n/source/edge.xml:2361
msgid ""
"Alternatively, <literal>GitRepo</literal> resources can also be used to "
"deploy <literal>SUC</literal> or <literal>SUC Plans</literal> on <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">air-gapped</emphasis> environments, <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">provided you mirror your repository setup through a local "
"git server</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"或者，<emphasis role=\"strong\">如果您通过本地 git 服务器镜像储存库设置</emph"
"asis>，则 <literal>GitRepo</literal> 资源也可用于在<emphasis role=\"strong\">"
"隔离</emphasis>环境中部署 <literal>SUC</literal> 或 <literal>SUC 计划</litera"
"l>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1854 l10n/source/edge.xml:2201
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2362 l10n/source/edge.xml:2698
msgid "Bundle"
msgstr "捆绑包"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1855 l10n/source/edge.xml:2363
msgid ""
"<literal>Bundles</literal> hold <emphasis role=\"strong\">raw</emphasis> "
"Kubernetes resources that will be deployed on the targeted cluster. Usually "
"they are created from a <literal>GitRepo</literal> resource, but there are "
"use-cases where they can be deployed manually. For more information refer to "
"the <link xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/bundle-add\">Bundle</link> "
"documentation."
msgstr ""
"<literal>捆绑包</literal>包含了要在目标群集上部署的<emphasis role=\"strong\""
">原始</emphasis> Kubernetes 资源。通常它们是基于 <literal>GitRepo</literal> "
"资源创建的，但在某些使用场景中也可以手动部署。有关详细信息，请参见<link "
"xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/bundle-add\">捆绑包</link>文档。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1856 l10n/source/edge.xml:2364
msgid ""
"In the context of \"Day 2\" operations, <literal>Bundle</literal> resources "
"are normally used to deploy <literal>SUC</literal> or <literal>SUC Plans</"
"literal> in <emphasis role=\"strong\">air-gapped</emphasis> environments "
"that do not use some form of <emphasis>local GitOps</emphasis> procedure "
"(e.g. a <emphasis role=\"strong\">local git server</emphasis>)."
msgstr ""
"在“Day 2”操作情境中，<literal>捆绑包</literal>资源通常用于在不使用某种形式的<"
"emphasis>本地 GitOps</emphasis> 过程（例如<emphasis role=\"strong\">本地 git "
"服务器</emphasis>）的<emphasis role=\"strong\">隔离</emphasis>环境中部署 "
"<literal>SUC</literal> 或 <literal>SUC 计划</literal>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1857 l10n/source/edge.xml:2365
msgid ""
"Alternatively, if your use-case does not allow for a <emphasis>GitOps</"
"emphasis> workflow (e.g. using a Git repository), <literal>Bundle</literal> "
"resources could also be used to deploy <literal>SUC</literal> or "
"<literal>SUC Plans</literal> in <emphasis role=\"strong\">non air-gapped</"
"emphasis> environments."
msgstr ""
"或者，如果您的应用场景不允许使用 <emphasis>GitOps</emphasis> 工作流程（例如需"
"使用 Git 储存库），则<literal>捆绑包</literal>资源也可用于在<emphasis role="
"\"strong\">非隔离</emphasis>环境中部署 <literal>SUC</literal> 或 "
"<literal>SUC 计划</literal>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
